com.camerontec.catalys.server.ordercache

Interface OrderCache

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<String>

    public interface OrderCache
extends Iterable<String>
    Interface representing the order cache.

    Iteration over the cache returns all ClOrdIDs ever inserted into the cache, including those associated with orders which have been subsequently deleted. The getMessage(String) method can be used to determined whether the message associated with that ClOrdID is still in the cache.

      • removeMessage

        IFIXMessage removeMessage(String key)
        Remove the message with the specified key.

        Note that this does not remove all traces of the keys associated with the message chain. Only clearMessages() clears all internal state.

        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        The removed message, or null if no such message existed.

      • getKeyChain

        List<String> getKeyChain(String key)
        Return the key chain associated with the specified key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        The key chain associated with the specified key in the original order added to the cache. This always contains the specified key even if there is no record of this key in the cache. This saves implementations from having to potentially do a linear search in order to detect whether the specified key is present or not.

      • onNewOrder

        void onNewOrder(IFIXMessage message,
                String scheduleCondition)
        Add a non duplicate new order message to the cache.

        If the message contains an already cached ClOrdID then the message is ignored.

        Parameters:
        message - The new order message. Must have non empty ClOrdID.
        scheduleCondition - The schedule condition which resulted in this message being added to the cache.

      • onAmendOrder

        void onAmendOrder(IFIXMessage message,
                  String scheduleCondition)
        Add a non duplicate new amend message to the cache.

        If the message contains an already cached ClOrdID then the message is ignored.

        Parameters:
        message - The new order message. Must have non empty ClOrdID and a non empty OrigClOrdID.
        scheduleCondition - The schedule condition which resulted in this message being added to the cache.

      • onCancelOrder

        void onCancelOrder(IFIXMessage message,
                   String scheduleCondition)

        Parameters:
        message - The cancel message. Must have a non empty OrigClOrdID.
        scheduleCondition - The schedule condition which resulted in this message being added to the cache.
